<html><DIV id=cdiv>
<P>Cyber Claw:
<P> 
<P> 
<P>Cyber Claw walked quietly through her forest. She was upset and sore. She didn't want to leave her forest, but she had to. If the two dinosaurs were Megatron's drones, then sooner or later, he would find out and come running to kill her. But she wasn't going to let that happen. 
<P>She snarled at the thoughts of him. Didn't he ever give up? Would he just leave her alone?
<P>But Predacons never left traitors alone. They would be chased down until they were dead. 
<P>This was her second hide-out. Now she was going to go for her third. She thought this place would be safe. But no. Maybe she would be better off  if she just left that other raptor alone. The problem was: she couldn't be safe if she knew it she was on Megatron side. They could ambush her with his fliers like before. 
<P>She didn't want to think about it, but there was no choice. She couldn't forget her past. It was apart of her, inbedded into her brain forever. Her confrontation with Dinobot, the beating she got from Megatron...her tretchery. It was who she was. 
<P>Cyber Claw paused. She looked left and right. Which way was she going to go? North? East? She snarled to herself. She could always activate her flight mode and try a way. 
<P>She shook her long head. Go North, she told herself. She had to try it. </P></DIV><p><hr>Get Your Private, Free E-mail from MSN Hotmail at <a href="http://www.hotmail.com/">http://www.hotmail.com</a><br></html>
